  "body": "# Problem\r\n### User story\r\nAs a user I want to cancel a pending transaction that is holding up other transactions\r\n\r\n#### Background\r\nPending transactions can be speed up by increasing the gas price for the ongoing transaction with the same nonce (see #9685). Alternatively, if the pending transaction is holding up other transactions, a user might want to cancel the pending transaction altogether. As long as the nonce is not confirmed, the tx can be canceled. \r\n\r\nTo do this, you can currently send a 0 ETH transaction, for example to yourself, with the same nonce. However:\r\n- Status currently does not allow editing the nonce to set it to the same nonce as the pending transaction\r\n- Status does not allow copying the nonce from a confirmed outgoing transaction or selecting a past transaction (with it's nonce) for actions (speed up, cancel).\r\n\r\n## Implementation\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n## Acceptance Criteria\r\nUI offers a `Cancel` transaction option that can be used without the user being required to know about or manually having to edit the nonce\r\n\r\n\r\n## Notes\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n## Future Steps\r\n\r\n",
